        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="8">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <para>The following procedure should be used when installing the fender extension reinforcements for
                    9100, 9200 and 9400 Model vehicles.
                </para>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Rear Fender Extension Splash Panel Removal</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">With the hood tilted open, remove hex nut, lockwasher, flat washer and hex bolt with
                        conical washer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Items 1 and 2, Figure 1</hotlnk>) securing the rear fender extension
                        splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Item 3, Figure 1</hotlnk>) to the side of the cab mounting bracket (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Item 4, Figure 1</hotlnk>), driver side shown. Save for
                        re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790701" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790701" filename="../afcfigures/g9790701.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. HEX NUT, FLAT WASHER AND LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. HEX BOLT WITH CONICAL WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CAB MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. HEX BOLT WITH CONICAL WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. CAB</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove hex bolts with conical washers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Item 5, Figure 1</hotlnk>) attaching the rear fender extension splash
                        panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Item 3, Figure 1</hotlnk>) to the underside of the cab (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790701">Item 6, Figure 1</hotlnk>) and remove the splash panel, driver side
                        shown. Save for re-installation.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Repeat this procedure to remove passenger side rear fender extension splash panel.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Preparation and Cleaning of Fender Extension and Reinforcement</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Thoroughly clean the inside area where the fender extension reinforcements (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790702">Items 1 and 2, Figure 2</hotlnk>) will be installed and wipe off with
                        a clean, dry, lint-free cloth.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790702" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790702" filename="../afcfigures/g9790702.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>OUTBOARD SIDE SHOWN</callout1>
                            <callout1>9200 REINFORCEMENT SHOWN</callout1>
                            <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION REINFORCEMENT, DRIVER SIDE (LEFT)</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. FENDER EXTENSION REINFORCEMENT, DRIVER SIDE (RIGHT)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Using coarse 60 Grit sandpaper, scuff the area on the rear fender extension splash
                        panels (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790703">Item 1, Figure 3</hotlnk>) where the fender extension reinforcement
                        will be installed (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790703">Item 2, Figure 3</hotlnk>), driver side shown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790703" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790703" filename="../afcfigures/g9790703.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. REINFORCEMENT MOUNTING SURFACE</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Fender extension reinforcements (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790702">Items 1 and 2, Figure 2</hotlnk>) are made for 9200 Models. If
                        installing on 9400 Models, the fender extension reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 1, Figure 4</hotlnk>) will need to be cut out for the cab
                        mounting bracket clearance opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 3, Figure 4</hotlnk>) and the mounting hole slot (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>) drilled out, driver side shown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790704" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790704" filename="../afcfigures/g9790704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"
                                 resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. CUT OUT FOR CAB MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CUT OUT FOR MOUNTING HOLE SLOT</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the fender extension reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 1, Figure 4</hotlnk>) inside rear fender extension splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 2, Figure 4</hotlnk>), self-locating. Hold it in place and check
                        scribe lines provided, from outside rear fender extension splash panel. If they do not match up
                        properly, make scribe lines for the cab mounting bracket clearance opening and mounting hole
                        slot (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Items 3 and 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>) in the fender extension
                        reinforcement, driver side shown.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Using a cutting tool, cut out the cab mounting bracket clearance opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 3, Figure 4</hotlnk>) and drill out the mounting hole slot (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>) in the fender extension reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790704">Item 1, Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Once cut and drilled, position the fender extension reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 1, Figure 5</hotlnk>) inside rear fender extension splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 2, Figure 5</hotlnk>), self-locating. Check the fit of cab
                        mounting bracket clearance opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 3, Figure 5</hotlnk>) and mounting hole slot (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 4, Figure 5</hotlnk>) in the rear fender extension splash panel,
                        driver side shown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790705" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790705" filename="../afcfigures/g9790705.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. CAB MOUNTING BRACKET CLEARANCE OPENING</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. MOUNTING HOLE SLOT</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Using coarse 60 Grit sandpaper, scuff the back side of the fender extension
                        reinforcements (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790702">Items 1 and 2, Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Using a clean, dry, lint-free cloth, wipe off any dust from both inside the rear
                        fender extension splash panels (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790703">Item 1, Figure 3</hotlnk>) where the fender extension reinforcement
                        will be installed (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790703">Item 2, Figure 3</hotlnk>) and rear side of the fender extension
                        reinforcements (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790702">Items 1 and 2, Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Fender Extension Reinforcement Installation</title>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Polyurethane/Epoxy adhesive causes allergic skin and respiratory reaction. Avoid contact
                            with eyes, skin and clothing. Avoid breathing vapor or mist. Do not breathe dust. Use with
                            adequate ventilation and appropriate breathing apparatus. Refer to Ciba-Geigy Corporation
                            Material Safety Data Sheet for Arathane AW 5540/41 before using this material. Ciba-Geigy
                            may be contacted by calling (517) 351-5900.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Apply Polyurethane/Epoxy adhesive on the rear side of the fender extension
                        reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 1, Figure 5</hotlnk>) and position it in place inside the rear
                        fender extension splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790705">Item 2, Figure 5</hotlnk>), driver side shown. Set up time for
                        adhesive is approximately 2 hours.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Hold the fender extension reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790706">Item 1, Figure 6</hotlnk>) in place inside the rear fender extension
                        splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790706">Item 2, Figure 6</hotlnk>) and drill the 7 holes for pop rivets (Item
                        3, Figure 6).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790706" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790706" filename="../afcfigures/g9790706.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. POP RIVET HOLES</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the 3/16 inch pop rivets (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790707">Item 2, Figure 7</hotlnk>) from outside the rear fender extension
                        splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790707">Item 1, Figure 7</hotlnk>), driver side shown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790707" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790707" filename="../afcfigures/g9790707.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>VIEW OUTSIDE DRIVER SIDE FENDER EXTENSION WITH REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                            <callout1>9400 SHOWN</callout1>
                            <callout1>1. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. POP RIVET, 3/16</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Rear Fender Extension Splash Panel Re-installation</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the rear fender extension splash panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 3, Figure 8</hotlnk>) in place on the underside of the cab (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 7, Figure 8</hotlnk>) and install four hex bolts with conical
                        washers and four new 5/16 X 1 inch O.D. flat washers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 5, Figure 8</hotlnk>) through the fender extension splash panel
                        into the cab, then install two hex bolts with conical washers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 6, Figure 8</hotlnk>) through the fender extension splash panel
                        into the mounting bracket, driver side shown.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790708" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790708" filename="../afcfigures/g9790708.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. HEX NUT, FLAT WASHER AND LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. HEX BOLT WITH CONICAL WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. REAR FENDER EXTENSION SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CAB MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. HEX BOLT WITH CONICAL WASHER AND 5/16 X 1 INCH FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. HEX BOLT WITH CONICAL WASHER</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. CAB</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install the hex bolt with conical washer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 2, Figure 8</hotlnk>) through the rear fender extension splash
                        panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 3, Figure 8</hotlnk>) and the side of the cab mounting bracket (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 4, Figure 8</hotlnk>), then install flat washer, lockwasher and
                        hex nut (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790708">Item 1, Figure 8</hotlnk>) securing the rear fender extension splash
                        panel to the cab mounting bracket, driver side shown.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Repeat this procedure to install passenger side rear fender extension splash
                        panel.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
        </svcproc>
